    <!-- SECTION 3: NETWORKS, INITIATIVES & PRACTICE -->
    <section>
      <div class="container--default">
        <p class="section-label fade-in">Networks, initiatives &amp; practice</p>
        <h2 class="section-title fade-in">Community and institutional resources</h2>

        <div class="pathways-grid fade-in">

          <div class="pathway-item">
            <div class="pathway-num" style="-webkit-text-stroke-color:var(--color-node-blue)">01</div>
            <h3>ITD Alliance — Global Alliance for Inter- and Transdisciplinarity</h3>
            <p>The global network connecting institutions, networks, and individuals working on ITD theory, method, and practice. Established in 2021, the Alliance organises working groups on pressing field-level questions — including Integration Experts and Expertise, and Toolkits &amp; Methods — and maintains curated resources covering journals, conferences, handbooks, and member publications. Open to institutions and individual members.</p>
            <a href="https://itd-alliance.org" class="service-card-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              Visit ITD Alliance
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="pathway-item">
            <div class="pathway-num" style="-webkit-text-stroke-color:var(--color-node-green)">02</div>
            <h3>ITD Alliance Working Group: Integration Experts and Expertise</h3>
            <p>The active community developing the recognition, training, and institutional frameworks for integration expertise. Organised around three output-oriented projects: the Value Project (recognising contributions of integration experts), the LTTI Project (learning, teaching and training integration), and an Integration Tools Project. The primary forum where research, policy, and practice on integration expertise is being developed and consolidated.</p>
            <a href="https://itd-alliance.org/working-groups/integration-experts/" class="service-card-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              Visit working group
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="pathway-item">
            <div class="pathway-num" style="-webkit-text-stroke-color:var(--color-node-purple)">03</div>
            <h3>i2Insights — Integration and Implementation Insights</h3>
            <p>A global, open, peer-curated blog and living resource repository publishing weekly contributions on concepts, methods, and frameworks for tackling complex real-world problems through research. Covers the full range of integration and implementation sciences topics — stakeholder engagement, knowledge synthesis, managing unknowns, supporting policy change, and more. The most actively maintained practical resource in the field.</p>
            <a href="https://i2insights.org" class="service-card-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              Visit i2Insights
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="pathway-item">
            <div class="pathway-num" style="-webkit-text-stroke-color:var(--color-node-amber)">04</div>
            <h3>SHAPE-ID: Shaping Interdisciplinary Practices in Europe</h3>
            <p>EU Horizon 2020 project (2019–2021, led by Trinity College Dublin) that produced toolkits, policy briefs, and recommendations for integrating Arts, Humanities, and Social Sciences (AHSS) into interdisciplinary and transdisciplinary research. Identified persistent structural barriers to integration in European research settings and co-produced guidance for funders, universities, and research teams on how to make interdisciplinary collaboration more deliberate and effective.</p>
            <a href="https://www.shapeidproject.eu" class="service-card-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              Visit SHAPE-ID
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="pathway-item">
            <div class="pathway-num" style="-webkit-text-stroke-color:var(--color-node-red)">05</div>
            <h3>Collaboration and Team Science: A Field Guide</h3>
            <p>National Cancer Institute (NCI), 2nd edition. Practical guide to building and managing collaborative science teams, grounded in the Science of Team Science (SciTS) field. Covers team formation, communication across disciplines, managing power and status dynamics, and assessing collaboration readiness. Widely used in health and biomedical research settings as onboarding material for new consortium members and as a framework for evaluating team function.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

